[[File:ModernEgypt, Saad Zaghloul, BAP 14781.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Famous portrait of [[Saad Zaghloul]] by Hanselman]]

'''W. Hanselman''' was a photographer of [[Jew]]ish origin established in [[Egypt]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Egypt: Dream and Realities |last=Beaugé |first=Gilbert |year=1993 |publisher=Aujourd'hui l'Égypte |location=Cairo |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rTZyAAAAMAAJ&q=Hanselman#search_anchor |format=snippet view |oclc=34120390 |accessdate=2009-07-23}}</ref> Working for [[Cairo]]'s Anglo-Swiss Studio, he was renowned for his images of King [[Fuad I of Egypt|Fuad I]], Queen [[Farida of Egypt|Farida]] and other Egyptian royalty.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Turner |first=Mia |date=16 June 2008|title=Nourab Keropian: The last of the Armenians |journal=[[The National (Abu Dhabi)|The National]] |url=http://www.azad-hye.net/article/article_view.asp?re=867fah44 |format=Reprint |accessdate=2010-02-20}}</ref> According to American photographer Barry Iverson (born in 1956), Hanselman was the great genius of court photography at the time and very much the favorite, particularly in the late 1920s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.adhamonline.com/Sony%20Gallery/King%20Fuad/Essay.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20030402133348/http://www.adhamonline.com/Sony%20Gallery/King%20Fuad/Essay.htm |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2003-04-02 |title=King Fouad At Work and Play |first=S. Abdallah |last=Schleifer |authorlink=Abdallah Schleifer |year=2001 |publisher=Kamal Adham Center for Journalism Training and Research |accessdate=2010-02-20 |df= }}</ref> One of his most recognizable works is a black-and-white photographic portrait of Egyptian nationalist leader and prime minister [[Saad Zaghloul]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Fahmi |first=Zaki |title=Safwat al-'Asr |trans-title=The Elite of Our Time |url=http://dar.bibalex.org/#DAR-Search%2F%28Title%3A%28%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%88%D8%A9%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B5%D8%B1%29%29%20AND%20%28AuthorName%3A%28%D8%B2%D9%83%D9%8A%20%D9%81%D9%87%D9%85%D9%8A%29%29 |accessdate=2010-02-10 |edition= |year=1995 |origyear=1926 |publisher=Madbouli Bookshop |location=Cairo |language=Arabic |oclc=318937678 |page=132}}</ref>

